04/04/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Police detained more suspects in its operation to track down members of the banned extremist Revolutionary People's Liberation Party Front (DHKP-C), the Anadolu Agency reported Saturday (3 April). Sources say at least eight more suspects were detained in Istanbul, Izmir and Bursa. That brings the total number to nearly 50, in addition to the 20 people detained during co-ordinated operations in Belgium, Germany, Italy and the Netherlands. The organisation is accused of murdering 100 policemen and soldiers and at least 80 civilians in numerous bombings. (Anadolu Agency, Reuters, AFP - 03/04/04)
